## Binding Pattern Reference

### Given step (setup, mutable context)
```rust
#[given("a server is running")]
fn given_server_running(ctx: &mut TestWorldMut) {
    let scenario = ctx.init();
    // Setup logic here
    scenario.server_start(config, protocol);
}
```

### When step (action, mutable context)  
```rust
#[when("a client connects")]
fn when_client_connects(ctx: &mut TestWorldMut) {
    let scenario = ctx.scenario_mut();
    // Action logic here
}
```

### Then step (assertion, immutable context)
```rust
#[then("the server has observed ConnectEvent")]
fn then_server_observed_connect(ctx: &TestWorldRef) -> AssertOutcome<()> {
    if ctx.server_observed(TrackedServerEvent::Connect) {
        AssertOutcome::Passed(())
    } else {
        AssertOutcome::Pending  // Keep polling
    }
}
```

